William Woodruff
Professor John Beckett writes:
William Woodruff's obituary (died September 25) states that "in 1946, he resumed his studies in economic history, at Oxford, and in 1950, became a member of Houblon-Norma research, while doing a BSc, an MA and a PhD".
That's what came out of Woodruff's letter in Beyond Nab End, but that's not correct.
